title: Dating App Matching Algorithm
description: Created a dating app matching algorithm that analyzes user preferences, interests, and behavioral patterns using advanced machine learning. It prioritizes compatibility by factoring in shared values, mutual goals, and personality traits, while leveraging real-time engagement data to suggest high-potential matches. This ensures users receive personalized, meaningful connections, promoting long-term compatibility over surface-level attraction.

title: Analyzing unicorn companies
description: Explored booming industries and investment opportunities using a MySQL database to analyze unicorn companies worth over $1 billion. Identified high-valuation sectors and examined annual new unicorn production from 2019 to 2021. Leveraged the rise of amateur investors and accessible trading platforms to understand global companies' financial performance for informed investment decisions.

title: League of Legends First Blood Statistical Analysis
description: Investigated the significance of the “first blood” event in League of Legends matches and its impact on match statistics and outcomes with various stages of analysis, starting from exploratory data analysis to hypothesis testing, creation of baseline models, and concluding with fairness analysis.

title: Optimizing Online Sports Retail Revenue
description: Maximized revenue for an online sports clothing company and extensively explored product data. Formulated recommendations that will help the company enhance its revenue. The dataset encompasses diverse information distributed across multiple tables, covering aspects such as prices, discounts, revenue, ratings, reviews, product descriptions, and website traffic.

title: Anime Recommender System
description: Created an anime recommender system with Python that leverages user viewing history, ratings, and preferences to suggest personalized anime recommendations. Using collaborative filtering, content-based filtering, or hybrid approaches, it identifies patterns between users and anime characteristics, ensuring tailored suggestions that match individual tastes and genres for an enhanced viewing experience.

title: Analyzing American baby name trends
description: What makes a name always liked or just popular for a short time? Looked at information from the U.S. Social Security Administration that goes back over a hundred years. Helped myself understand what names people in America have liked for their babies over time.

title: Blood Bank Management
description: Managed a blood bank dataset through SQL, oversaw blood types, donors, recipients, and units. Demonstrated expertise in healthcare data handling, optimizing blood supply, and ensuring timely availability. Demonstrated skills in data management and analysis within the sensitive environment of a blood bank.

title: Sentiment Analysis in Stock News Headlines
description: Completed a sentiment analysis project in Python evaluates stock news headlines to assess their impact on market sentiment. By using Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques, it classifies headlines as positive, negative, or neutral. The project can integrate sentiment scores with stock price data to help predict market movements and assist in data-driven trading decisions.

title: Mental Health in the Tech Industry
description: Studied employee data in the IT business, focusing on their perspectives on mental health. Investigated and analyzed attitudes of mental health, as well as the prevalence of mental health illnesses, particularly in the technology industry.

title: Analyzing Carbon Emissions
description: In today's world, where people care about the environment, this project helps to look at information about carbon emissions. Checked data on carbon emissions, how much energy was used, and renewable energy sources. Used SQL to see how emissions have changed over time, see if policies or efforts are working, and came up with ideas to reduce your carbon footprint.

title: Analyzing motorcycle parts sales
description: Explored the data of a company that sells motorcycle parts. Gained insights into their wholesale sales over time across three warehouse sites, assisting in understanding the revenue streams better. Determined how much net revenue the company will generate across its product lines each month and at each warehouse.

title: Employee payroll management system
description: Developed a comprehensive Payroll Management System , leveraging the NYC Payroll dataset to facilitate efficient tracking, analysis, and reporting of employee salary and related information.
